postNum14.image-text:
The health department in Massachusetts has recently mandated all children, from 6 months through college, must have the flu shot to go to school. Their rationale is to avoid crowded hospitals if there is a “bad flu season.” Does this sound familiar? And is this a foreshadowing of what’s to come if a COVID vaccine becomes available?  Jefferey Jaxen reports.

Story correction: Massachusetts bill H.3999 aiming to remove religious exemptions to vaccination was defeated.
